@Fiskerallin I would consider buying leap calls at or near the money. Each contract represents 100 shares and goes up or down (with velocity) based on how close or far away from the strike price you are. 

I own Fisker calls expiring April 2024 and Jan 2025 at $3, $5, $7, $10 and $15. I'll take profits on the 2024 calls once $FSR runs, and then use the profits to buy more 2025 leap calls or shares. 

You have to watch options and take profits when you're up (before the expiration date). Other than that, it's pretty straight forward. Some risk involved but basically it's a long term bet you think Fisker will be worth more in a year (or two) than it is now.

@howardlindzon @MetalChris in general I like buying sports betting companies as an investment idea. FanDuel IPO likely coming in Q4. They own 45% of US betting market.. followed by Draft Kings (20%), Caesars, MGM.

My current positions are $DKNG and $MGM (overweight) with a small position in $PENN. The total market for sports betting will reach between $12 and $17B in 2025. I would be interested in any additional insights you have on the space. Thanks

